name: A collection of fragmented existences #7
description:
Unraveling our own genome like pulling threads from the fabric,
looking for meaning in chemical bonds, and breaking synapses.
We are children of the sun, of the water, of the infinite sky.
From empty space in a double helix.
We look for meaning, without knowing if there is one. Luis Ponce 2021. 2160px · 25FPS · 24F · 1920X1080px version available.
